spec: socket_extra154
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(socket)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html — Python socket module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/socket.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/socketmodule.c"
    - "socket_extra153.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket.send/__recv/__accept/__close/__fileno qualnames and qualname lengths (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra152.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket.__name__/__module__/__bases__[0].__name__ / socket.socket.connect/__bind/__listen qualnames / socket.error.__name__.__eq__('OSError') / socket.gaierror.__name__/__module__ (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra151.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.AF_INET/AF_INET6/AF_UNIX/SOCK_STREAM/SOCK_DGRAM enum values (table + invariants)."
    - "socket.zspec / early extras — cover socket.__name__/__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in socket_extra93 through socket_extra153."
    - "Wave 336 theme: socket module exception class hierarchy — socket.error.__name__.__eq__('OSError') / socket.gaierror.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__('OSError') / socket.herror.__name__.__eq__('herror') / socket.herror.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__('OSError') / socket.timeout.__name__.__eq__('TimeoutError') / socket.timeout.__module__.__eq__('builtins') / socket.timeout.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__('OSError')."
    - "socket.error.__name__ == 'OSError'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.gaierror.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'OSError'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.herror.__name__ == 'herror'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.herror.__module__ == 'socket'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.herror.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'OSError'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.timeout.__name__ == 'TimeoutError'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.timeout.__module__ == 'builtins'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.timeout.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'OSError'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: socket.gaierror.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'OSError'. socket.gaierror is a subclass of OSError (socket.error). extra152 anchors gaierror.__name__=='gaierror' and gaierror.__module__=='socket'; this spec anchors gaierror.__bases__[0].__name__ as the first __bases__ anchor for gaierror in this series."
    - "Note: socket.herror.__name__ == 'herror' (6 chars). socket.herror is the exception for host-related errors from gethostbyname() and related functions. Like gaierror, herror is a proper subclass of OSError. Its __name__ is 'herror' (lowercase, 6 chars), its __module__ is 'socket' (6 chars), and its base class is OSError. herror is distinct from gaierror: herror is for legacy gethostbyname() errors; gaierror is for the newer getaddrinfo() errors."
    - "Note: socket.timeout.__name__ == 'TimeoutError' (12 chars). CRITICAL: socket.timeout is an alias for the built-in TimeoutError, NOT a class with __name__=='timeout'. In Python 3.3+, socket.timeout was unified with the built-in TimeoutError (PEP 3151). So socket.timeout.__name__ == 'TimeoutError' (12 chars, capital T and E) and socket.timeout.__module__ == 'builtins' (8 chars). socket.timeout is TimeoutError evaluates to True. socket.timeout.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'OSError' because TimeoutError inherits from OSError."
    - "Note: socket.timeout.__module__ == 'builtins' (8 chars). Because socket.timeout is an alias for the built-in TimeoutError, its __module__ is 'builtins' — not 'socket' as one might expect. This is analogous to socket.error.__module__ being 'builtins' (since socket.error IS OSError, which is a built-in). Both socket.error and socket.timeout have __module__ == 'builtins', while socket.gaierror and socket.herror have __module__ == 'socket'."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

