table socket_extra154.herror_base_and_timeout_identity:
  description: "socket.herror.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__('OSError')==True / timeout.__name__.__eq__('TimeoutError')==True / timeout.__module__.__eq__('builtins')==True / timeout.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__('OSError')==True — herror.__bases__[0] is OSError (herror subclasses OSError like gaierror); socket.timeout IS TimeoutError alias (__name__=='TimeoutError', 12 chars, NOT 'timeout'); timeout.__module__=='builtins' (8 chars; built-in class; contrasts with gaierror/herror which have __module__=='socket'); timeout.__bases__[0] is OSError (TimeoutError inherits from OSError per PEP 3151); first sockexc154 anchor for herror.__bases__ and timeout identity"
  kind: python_call_eq
